  "description": "<p>Take on the most demanding backcountry adventures. Styled with a nod to the classic 1991 MEC Icefield Jacket, the upgraded APEX Icefield features best-in-class materials and tech that defines the modern standards of ski touring shells. Toray's electrospun membrane technology is close to 50% more breathable than standard 3-layer jackets while being just as waterproof, keeping you comfortable while skinning and protected during alpine storms or tumbles.</p><ul><li>3-layer Toray\u00ae electrospun membrane provides 10,000mm waterproof protection and incredibly high breathability</li><li>Fully seam-taped construction keeps you dry and comfortable in howling conditions</li><li>Articulated arms and patterning ensures unrestricted movement</li><li>YKK\u00ae AquaGuard\u00ae Vislon zippers throughout</li><li>Underarm vents have 2-way zippers to release heat</li><li>Contoured cuffs layer well with gloves and close with Velcro\u00ae tabs</li><li>Large front pockets sit high for backpack and harness compatibility</li><li>Shock-cord adjustable hem seals out snow and drafts</li><li>Built-in Recco\u00ae Rescue System reflector allows ski patrol and mountain rescue teams to detect and locate it under snow</li><li>Internal label shares the story and history behind the jacket</li><li>Pairs perfectly with the APEX Salopettes for a backcountry-ready system</li></ul>",
